"2:230:17" : {s: 2, a: 230, w: 17, r: "", t: "أَن", l: "أَن", lc: 577, tl: "an", lb: "যে, যেন",e: "if", b: "যেন/যে", i: "bahwa", f: 462, rm: ""},
"2:230:18" : {s: 2, a: 230, w: 18, r: "رجع", t: "يَتَرَاجَعَآ", l: "يَتَرَاجَعَ", lc: 1, tl: "yatarājaʿā", lb: "ফিরে আসা, ফেরৎ আসা, পিছনে পড়া",e: "they return to each other", b: "পরস্পরের কাছে ফিরে আসতে", i: "keduanya ruju' (kawin kembali)", f: 1, rm: "to return, turn back, turn off, (blame) upon any one, come back, repeat, answer, bring answer, be brought back. rajiun - one who returns. murjiun - return, termination. tarajaa (vb. 6)  -to return to one another."},
"2:230:19" : {s: 2, a: 230, w: 19, r: "", t: "إِن", l: "إِن", lc: 690, tl: "in", lb: "যদি, কেবলমাত্র, শুধুই",e: "if", b: "যদি", i: "jika", f: 253, rm: ""},
"2:230:20" : {s: 2, a: 230, w: 20, r: "ظنن", t: "ظَنَّآ", l: "ظَنَّ", lc: 47, tl: "ẓannā", lb: "মনে করা, ভাবা, ধারণা/ অনুমান করা",e: "they believe", b: "দুজনেই মনে করে", i: "keduanya berpendapat", f: 1, rm: "To think, suppose, doubt, assume, deem, believe, know, imagine, suspect, conjunctive, be sure of something in view of ones observations. As a general rule often this verb is succeeded by anna or an, that means to be sure about."},
"2:230:21" : {s: 2, a: 230, w: 21, r: "", t: "أَن", l: "أَن", lc: 577, tl: "an", lb: "যে, যেন",e: "that", b: "যেন/যে", i: "bahwa", f: 462, rm: ""},
"2:230:22" : {s: 2, a: 230, w: 22, r: "قوم", t: "يُقِيمَا", l: "أَقَامَ", lc: 54, tl: "yuqīmā", lb: "দৃঢ়ভাবে স্থাপন করা",e: "they (will be able to) keep", b: "দুজনে রক্ষা করতে পারবে", i: "keduanya melaksanakan", f: 3, rm: "stand still or firm, rose/stand up, managed/conducted/ordered/regulated/superintended, established, made it straight/right, maintain/erect/observe/perform, set up, people/community/company, abode, stature/dignity/rank. aqama - to keep a thing or an affair in a right state."},
"2:230:23" : {s: 2, a: 230, w: 23, r: "حدد", t: "حُدُودَ", l: "حُدُود", lc: 14, tl: "ḥudūda", lb: "সীমাসমূহ",e: "(the) limits", b: "সীমারেখাগুলো", i: "hukum-hukum", f: 6, rm: "To define a limit, determine (a thing), punish (a culprit), prevent, thrust back, throw back, sharpen. To hinder/impede/restrain, to debar or withhold or forbid/prohibit, to interdict, repel/turn away/avert, inflict castigation or punishment, distinguish or separate one thing from another by a mark or note, edge or sharpen a knife, look sharply or intently or attentively at a person or thing, to be sharp [or effective] in respect of eloquence or intellect or understanding or anger."},
"2:230:24" : {s: 2, a: 230, w: 24, r: "اله", t: "ٱللَّهِ", l: "ٱللَّه", lc: 2811, tl: "l-lahi", lb: "আল্লাহ",e: "(of) Allah", b: "আল্লাহর", i: "Allah", f: 940, rm: "to serve, worship or adore; to protect, grant refuge, preserve save, rescue, liberate; object of worship ie God; (ا-ل-ل-ه) God, the one true God applied as a proper name denoting the true god, comprising all the excellent divine names; a unity comprising all the essences of existing things."},
"2:230:25" : {s: 2, a: 230, w: 25, r: "", t: "وَتِلْكَ", l: "ذَٰلِك", lc: 520, tl: "watilka", lb: "ওটা",e: "And these", b: "এবং এটা", i: "dan itulah", f: 11, rm: ""},
"2:230:26" : {s: 2, a: 230, w: 26, r: "حدد", t: "حُدُودُ", l: "حُدُود", lc: 14, tl: "ḥudūdu", lb: "সীমাসমূহ",e: "(are the) limits", b: "সীমাসমূহ", i: "hukum-hukum", f: 6, rm: "To define a limit, determine (a thing), punish (a culprit), prevent, thrust back, throw back, sharpen. To hinder/impede/restrain, to debar or withhold or forbid/prohibit, to interdict, repel/turn away/avert, inflict castigation or punishment, distinguish or separate one thing from another by a mark or note, edge or sharpen a knife, look sharply or intently or attentively at a person or thing, to be sharp [or effective] in respect of eloquence or intellect or understanding or anger."},
"2:230:27" : {s: 2, a: 230, w: 27, r: "اله", t: "ٱللَّهِ", l: "ٱللَّه", lc: 2811, tl: "l-lahi", lb: "আল্লাহ",e: "(of) Allah", b: "আল্লাহর", i: "Allah", f: 940, rm: "to serve, worship or adore; to protect, grant refuge, preserve save, rescue, liberate; object of worship ie God; (ا-ل-ل-ه) God, the one true God applied as a proper name denoting the true god, comprising all the excellent divine names; a unity comprising all the essences of existing things."},
"2:230:28" : {s: 2, a: 230, w: 28, r: "بين", t: "يُبَيِّنُهَا", l: "بَيَّنُ", lc: 35, tl: "yubayyinuhā", lb: "স্পষ্ট",e: "He makes them clear", b: "তা তিনি স্পষ্ট বর্ণনা করেন", i: "Dia menerangkannya", f: 1, rm: ""},
"2:230:29" : {s: 2, a: 230, w: 29, r: "قوم", t: "لِقَوْمٍۢ", l: "قَوْم", lc: 383, tl: "liqawmin", lb: "লোকেরা, জনগোষ্ঠী",e: "to a people", b: "(সেই) লোকদের জন্য", i: "bagi kaum", f: 15, rm: "stand still or firm, rose/stand up, managed/conducted/ordered/regulated/superintended, established, made it straight/right, maintain/erect/observe/perform, set up, people/community/company, abode, stature/dignity/rank. aqama - to keep a thing or an affair in a right state."},
"2:230:30" : {s: 2, a: 230, w: 30, r: "علم", t: "يَعْلَمُونَ", l: "عَلِمَ", lc: 382, tl: "yaʿlamūna", lb: "(সে) জানে",e: "who know", b: "তারা জানে", i: "mereka mengetahui", f: 81, rm: "to mark/sign/distinguish, creations/beings, world, science/learning/knowledge/information, aware/know. By means of which one knows a thing, hence it signifies world or creation, because by it the Creator is known. alim (pl. ulama) - one who is learned/wise or knows."},
